com.github.rolecraftdev.guild

Class GuildManager

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.github.rolecraftdev.guild.GuildManager

  • public final class GuildManager
extends Object
    Stores Guild data and Guild-related configuration options and manages Guilds in Rolecraft.

    • Method Detail

      • addGuild

        public boolean addGuild(Guild guild,
               boolean fromDatabase)
        Adds the given Guild object to the Set of loaded Guilds if it is valid - i.e if it is loaded from the database or doesn't clash with another Guild. (being logically equal)
        Parameters:
        guild - - The Guild to load
        fromDatabase - - Used internally for loading from database, always use false
        Returns:
        True for success, false if the Guild already exists

      • removeGuild

        public boolean removeGuild(Guild guild)
        Attempts to delete the given Guild, both from memory and from the SQL database. This method will fail if this GuildManager hasn't loaded yet.
        Parameters:
        guild - - The Guild to remove
        Returns:
        True if the Guild was removed, false if it wasn't

      • getGuild

        public Guild getGuild(String name)
        Gets the Guild object that has the specified name.
        Parameters:
        name - - The name of the wanted Guild
        Returns:
        The Guild with the given name if it is contained by this GuildManager, or null if none is found, or this manager has not finished loading

      • getPlayerGuild

        public Guild getPlayerGuild(UUID player)
        Gets the Guild the given player belongs to.
        Parameters:
        player - - The unique identifier of the player to get the Guild of
        Returns:
        The given player's Guild, or null if they don't have one. Note that this will also return null if this GuildManager hasn't been fully loaded yet
